				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/3.14-19?lang=spa#13" target="_blank">Efesios 3:14&ndash;19</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/col/2.6-7?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">Colosenses 2:6&ndash;7</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote4-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote4-24985_002_013">4.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.15?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 128:15</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote5-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote5-24985_002_013">5.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.18?lang=spa#17" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 128:18</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote6-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote6-24985_002_013">6.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">Los Art&iacute;culos de Fe formaban parte de una carta dirigida al se&ntilde;or John Wentworth, editor y propietario de un peri&oacute;dico de Chicago; se public&oacute; por primera vez en el peri&oacute;dico <span class="emphasis">Times and Seasons</span>, 1&ordm; de marzo de 1842; V&eacute;ase <span class="emphasis">Ensign</span>, julio de 2002, p&aacute;gs. 26&ndash;32.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote7-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote7-24985_002_013">7.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">En ese documento tambi&eacute;n se mencionan dones del Esp&iacute;ritu que iluminan la vida de los miembros de la Iglesia. Se predicen grandes acontecimientos de los &uacute;ltimos d&iacute;as, como la restauraci&oacute;n de las diez tribus, el establecimiento de Si&oacute;n y el reinado milenario de Cristo sobre la tierra renovada. El documento contiene principios de libertad de religi&oacute;n, de tolerancia y de obediencia a la ley; y concluye con una expresi&oacute;n pertinente a nuestra percepci&oacute;n de la vida y de ideales personales elevados.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote8-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote8-24985_002_013">8.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/23.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">Alma 23:6</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote9-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote9-24985_002_013">9.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/jacob/6.7-9?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">Jacob 6:7&ndash;9</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote10-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote10-24985_002_013">10.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase, por ejemplo, <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/3.6-7?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">2 Nefi 3:6&ndash;7</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote11-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote11-24985_002_013">11.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/7.20?lang=spa#19" target="_blank">Mateo 7:20</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/14.20?lang=spa#19" target="_blank">3 Nefi 14:20</a>; v&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n <a href="http://scriptures.byu.edu/getscrip.php?ID=43262">TJS, Mateo 7:25</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote12-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote12-24985_002_013">12.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/gal/5.22?lang=spa#21" target="_blank">G&aacute;latas 5:22</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote13-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote13-24985_002_013">13.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><span class="emphasis">Stand Ye in Holy Places</span>, 1974, p&aacute;gs. 218&ndash;219.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote14-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote14-24985_002_013">14.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.36?lang=spa#35" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 93:36</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote15-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote15-24985_002_013">15.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/mal/3.10?lang=spa#9" target="_blank">Malaqu&iacute;as 3:10</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/24.10?lang=spa#9" target="_blank">3 Nefi 24:10</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote16-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote16-24985_002_013">16.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/89.18-21?lang=spa#17" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 89:18–21</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote17-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote17-24985_002_013">17.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/15.3-5?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Juan 15:3&ndash;5</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote18-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote18-24985_002_013">18.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/3.17?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">Efesios 3:17</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote19-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote19-24985_002_013">19.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/isa/64.8?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">Isa&iacute;as 64:8</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote20-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote20-24985_002_013">20.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/13.1-5?lang=spa#0" target="_blank">Alma 13:1&ndash;5</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote21-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote21-24985_002_013">21.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.63?lang=spa#62" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 132:63</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote22-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote22-24985_002_013">22.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">&ldquo;As&iacute; como Abraham&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/101.4?lang=spa#3" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 101:4</a>). V&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/heb/11.17?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">Hebreos 11:17</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote23-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote23-24985_002_013">23.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/1.39?lang=spa#38" target="_blank">Mois&eacute;s 1:39</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote24-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote24-24985_002_013">24.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.68?lang=spa#67" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 88:68</a>. Cuando se obtiene cualquier bendici&oacute;n de Dios, &ldquo;es porque se obedece aquella ley sobre la cual se basa&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/130.21?lang=spa#20" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 130:21</a>).</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote25-24985_002_013"><a name="-24985_002_013">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote25-24985_002_013">25.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/15.16?lang=spa#15" target="_blank">Juan 15:16</a>.</p>
			</li> </ol>
                                            
